724958f-d.text:
2nd Street, east side, between 27th and Astoria Avenue, showing the Judge Munson House, a stone structure built in 1840 by Stephen A. Halsey. It was occupied by Captain Munson in 1866. From 1889 to 1896 the house was the Long Island City High School and later became Public School No. 9. E. L. Armbruster is authority for the above data.

Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1923

View 3: George D. Chinn  April, 1940

View 4: P.L.Sperr  March 13, 1931

724956f-a.text:
End Street, at and adjoining the Northeast Corner of 27th Ave. (foreground), showing in the foreground the Wade house. Beyond it was the home of Benjamin S.H. Maillefert from 1867-1882. Here Elizabeth his daughter married Fred Mackill.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
